yet beautiful. Ces’ thoughts and opinions about tattoos break up the narration of her tale to offer an insight into her deeper thoughts on the matter.</p> <p>I think that everyone should read this book at some point as it has taught me a lot about victimisation and how people do not want that to be their defining feature. As well as how, despite the most difficult circumstances, it is possible to pull through and move on.</p> <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">How do I get involved in the Guardian children's books site?</a> </p> </aside>  <ul> <li><strong>Find out more about the book on the <a href=\"http://deirdresullivanbooks.com/needlework/\">author’s website</a>.</strong></li> </ul> <h2><strong>Want to tell the world about a book you’ve read? <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">Join the site</a> and send us your review!</strong></h2>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4gcfx","wordcount":"200","standfirst":"<p>‘Needlework is a powerful book that deals with difficult subject matter’</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/2016/feb/17/needlework-deirdre-sullivan-review","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/childrens-books-site/2016/feb/17/needlework-deirdre-sullivan-review","sectionName":"Children's books","elements":[{"id":"56b3bfd4ae678c0c5158d76a69a2a5703c568945","relation":"body","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/56b3bfd4ae678c0c5158d76a69a2a5703c568945/0_0_309_475/309.jpg","typeData":{"role":"thumbnail","mediaApiUri":"https://api.media.gutools.co.uk/images/56b3bfd4ae678c0c5158d76a69a2a5703c568945","altText":"Needlework","caption":"","source":"PR","credit":"Photograph: PR","mediaId":"56b3bfd4ae678c0c5158d76a69a2a5703c5689