rth buying for a friend or family member of any age. </p> <p>Out of the many stories in this collection my top two would HAVE to be The World’s Greatest Teen Detective by Derek Landy (Yay Skulduggery Pleasant!) and The Bear by John Connolly. While Landy’s writing is very humorous and quite obviously written with that in mind, Connolly’s is more serious, heartfelt and quite adorable.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image element--thumbnail\" data-media-id=\"b7edbb3a46159f4b3eaaea9293d495164484f090\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/b7edbb3a46159f4b3eaaea9293d495164484f090/0_0_358_499/358.jpg\" alt=\"Once Upon a Place\" width=\"358\" height=\"499\" class=\"gu-image\" /> </figure>  <p>The. Illustrations. Are. AMAZING! The front cover is beautiful in full colour and black and white drawings feature through each story or poem. All illustrations are by P. J. Lynch, and they’re incredibly detailed and realistic, which aids the storytelling and helps suck you into the stories. This collection wouldn’t be the same without these magnificent illustrations.</p> <p>All in all, Once Upon a Place is a must for anyone, as a gift or just for yourself. I rate it 9½ out of 10.</p> <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">How do I get involved in the Guardian children's books site?</a> </p> </aside>  <h2><strong>Want to tell the world about a book you’ve read? <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">Join the site</a> and send us your review!</strong></h2>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4gcd2","wordcount":"218","standfirst":"<p>‘a beautiful collection of stories and poems’</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/2016/feb/16/once-upon-a-place-eoin-colfer-review","apiUrl":"http://content.gu